Maybe you don't feel you have anyone. If you don't yet, that's ok. Maybe you feel completely alone and think no one will understand or you've been hurt before and aren't ready to trust anyone. I get it..I've been there. But there is hope still for you to be able to see what you currently can't.\
\
For obvious reasons the best person to ask these questions to are The Lord. He KNOWS EVERYTHING, IS EVERYWHERE, and can DO ANYTHING.  The best part of all this He is also ALL LOVING. As a heavenly Father, He wants the best for you. He cares for you and wants to speak into your life in ways maybe you haven't allowed Him before.\
\
This may be a little weird for you, asking God to speak to you. Depending on how pentecostal you are, you may be tempted to put the book down now and move on to something a little more safe. But, before you do that just hear me out.\
\
That same chapter that James gives us the script for our life, he also gives the formula for moving forward.  \
\
He says: \
