James tells us that God's word is like a mirror. That it has the ability to show us and speak to us about what we need to change and do differently in life. \
\
This is great news for those who aren't' ready or don't have anyone to show them what they need to change. What this passage and others say is that through reading God's word we can allow God's Spirit to convict and challenge us to make the changes we need to make. \
\
If you currently don't spend time in God's Word daily I want to encourage you to make that a priority. I believe with all of my heart that as we read God's Word it reads us. It the primary way God uses to speak to His people about their lives and their future.\
\
Many people want to hear the voice of God but don't want to read what He's already said. I don't know who said it first but the phrase of "If you want to hear God speak read His Word, if you want to hear God speak audibly read it aloud" is perfect and true. When we spend time reading what God has already said we honor the past and trust God will use it to speak into our future.\
\
But the passage isn't a blessing but a warning. If you read it, James is really warning us against a false sense of spiritual growth and understanding. He says there is a way to read God's word, know what it says, feel better about ourselves, think we are moving forward but really we just fooling ourselves. \
\
In fact James says you can deceive yourself if you just read or listen to God's word and think you're better. \
\
While I think we all can agree that someone actually has to change their life in order for change to come about, I've struggle with the analogy that James uses. Who in their right mind uses a mirror, looks at their face, sees what needs to be done and then doesn't do anything about it? \
\
I've seen the opposite. I've seen people who spend way too much time looking, primping, plucking, combing, and all sort of other techniques to ensure they look as good as they could in front of others. But the opposite?\
\
I struggled with this until one day I did it. I was in hurry and while I don't spend hours in front of the mirror I will admit I don't like to look poorly in front of others. So before I left I checked the mirror really quick. I was late and had to leave but couldn't without at least having a quick look. I looked terrible. I had just woken up and my hair was an absolute mess. \
\
I had a problem. I had to leave, I was already running late for the meeting. I looked like complete trash (make funny here) and my vanity was preventing me from just blowing it off. Solution? I grabbed a hat!\
\
It's not revolutionary in any way, in fact that is what hats do. They cover our heads so people can't see what is underneath. And while that day I covered my hair with a hat, there are countless I've covered my own sin, struggles, temptations, or as we're calling them in this book alligators with a spiritual hat.\
\
I see the issues in my life but for a number of reasons, I don't want to or have time to deal with it right now. I'll deal with it tomorrow or at later that day.\
\
I think we all do this. We have the ability to read God's word, allow it to convict us of the things in our lives that need to be changed, and yet often we put on spiritual hats.\
\
(I could finish this section with all the different type of hats we put on but not sure I need it here)\
\
So before you move on to the next chapter? Before maybe you move past the conviction of the questions we've read together here. Is there something you're covering up with a spiritual hat? \
\
